snippet.textDisplay:
Shikwa is perhaps the best thing to ever happen to Poetry and anyone who compare Ghalib and Iqbal must read this Kalam to come to a conclusion. 

They should’ve invited Tina Sani or Fariha Parvez to recite this since they decided to set Shikwa at a slower tempo than usual. Nonetheless, a really good composition! 
Fareed Ayaz & Party are my favorite and the way they’re always open to giving newer singers and instruments a chance is beautiful.
snippet.textOriginal:
